snippet.textDisplay:
Whatever you do, if you have a firearm? Keep one magazine labeled as “End of the Journey” for those hopeless situations. Rather not have a zombino running around in an EOD suit.

Also, remember this. Suppressors can only take so much damage before they break. There are multiple videos of suppressors overheating from automatic usage. Hell, there’s one of an M249 SAW with a suppressor that melts after heavy usage. It MELTS. They can only take so much punishment, always have a spare on you.
